7: *   with structured output routing (standard, skill, or generic update)
120:			return "AGENTS.md is a universal AI agent documentation file. Standards are added as inline sections. Skills are placed in `.agents/skills/<skill-name>/`.";
122:			return "Claude Code uses CLAUDE.md as its main documentation file. Standards are stored as rule files in `.claude/rules/<standard-slug>.md` with YAML frontmatter. Skills are placed in `.claude/skills/<skill-name>/`.";
124:			return "GitHub Copilot uses `.github/copilot-instructions.md` as its main documentation file. Standards are stored as instruction files in `.github/instructions/<standard-slug>.md` with YAML frontmatter. Skills are placed in `.github/skills/<skill-name>/`.";
140:/** Per-agent output type instructions for standards, skills, and generic updates. */
145:	const skillInstructions = getSkillInstructions(targetAgent);
155:**Generic Update** — A direct addition or edit to \`${genericFile}\`. Use for content that doesn't fit standards or skills (e.g., project structure, setup steps, architecture notes).
